Merge pull request #182 from roncapat/python-fixes

* added "serial" library dependency in setup.py
* simplified some code
* fixed some bugs
* removed error parameter, because in Python integers are immutable values and if modified inside 
* functions, the new value will no more be tied to the outer scope
* renamed id to dxl_id, as id is a python builtin
* removed unnecessary deallocations (Python has a garbage collector)

data.author: Jeff McBride
data.message:
Don't flush the TX buffer right before transmit

This causes random trucated writes, where only 1 or 2 bytes of the packet
are transmitted by the USB serial chip. I'm not exactly sure why; perhaps
there is some kind of buffering that causes the flush command and write
command to make it to the USB device out-of-order.

In any case, I cannot see any reason why a flush should be necessary,
especially on the TX buffer, so it's easy to remove
